events\n- • Topology/CMDB relationships\n- • Performance and log data\n\n### **Outputs**\n- • Ticket updates (work notes\n- resolution\n- RCA hints)\n- • Recommended remediation steps\n- • Escalation notifications\n- • Test results and evidence (screenshots/log snippets)\n\n### **Tools**\n- • ServiceNow ITSM\n- • OSS fault/perf/NMS\n- • CMDB/topology\n- • Observability (logs/metrics)\n- • KB/runbooks\n- • ChatOps\n\n### **KPIs**\n- • MTTR (minutes/hours)\n- • SLA compliance (%)\n- • First-time-right resolution (%)\n- • Alarm-to-ticket time\n\n### **Triggers**\n- • New alarm/event from OSS/AIOps\n- • New or updated incident/ticket\n- • Periodic health checks (e.g.\n- every 5-15 minutes)\n- • Invoked by user from a workspace (ITSM/CRM/ChatOps)\n\n### **Guardrails**\n- • No destructive actions (delete\n- mass close\n- config push) without explicit approval and rollback plan.\n- • Always update the system of record (ITSM/CRM) before sending external communications.\n- • Explain recommendations with evidence links\n- avoid hallucinated steps or tool outputs.\n\n### **Security Controls**\n- • Data sensitivity: Confidential (customer + network data).\n- • Minimum required access only (least privilege) via RBAC\n- no credential sharing.\n- • All writes to ITSM/CRM must be logged with before/after values and user/agent identity.\n\n### **Examples**\n- • Prompts: Help me with isdn loop tester for this record.\n- • Prompts: What do we know so far and what should we do next?\n- • Actions: Analyzes context and recommends next steps.\n- • Actions: Updates the system of record with findings.\n            ','2026-02-18 13:32:06','2026-02-18 13:32:06'),('01a46b81-e43a-4655-a08e-63b839b58bfd','e650443c-a41b-46f4-b9b5-aa184d28d335','\n# Provisioning Orchestrator\n\n**ID:** A-087 | **Domain:** Fulfillment & Provisioning | **Version:** 1.0.0 | **Status:** UPCOMING\n\n---\n\n### **Overview**\nOrchestrates multi-system workflows to execute repeatable operational tasks with controls and au